&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Here is my list:
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; - File based integration (coordination of processes using the file system)
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; - Database based integration (coordination of processes using an RDBMS
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; - Message Queues
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; - RPC (I am equating all forms of it: RMI, DCOM, Corba, WS-*, URI tunneling. Makes sense?[1])
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; - PubSub
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; - HTTP Type I ( HTTP with design time WADL or similar and generic media types)
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; - HTTP Type II ( HTTP with design time WADL or similar and specific media types)
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; - REST
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Anything else?
